.TH WAYLAND-DISPLAY-INFO 1 "July 2025" "1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
wayland-display-info \- monitor Wayland outputs and write /var/cache/wayland-display-info/display-info
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wayland-display-info
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wayland-display-info
continuously queries wlroots compositors via the
.BR wlr-output-management
protocol and writes one line per connected output to the cache file.

.PP
The DPI figure reflects the actual visible pixel density:

.IP \[bu] 2
\fBRotation neutral\fR – rotating a monitor by 90 ° or 270 ° does not change its
pixel density, so no adjustment is necessary.

.IP \[bu] 2
\fBLetter-/pillar-boxing aware\fR – if the chosen mode’s aspect ratio differs
from the panel’s native ratio and the compositor adds black bars, the daemon
reports the larger of the horizontal or vertical DPI, keeping the value stable
for the fully used axis.

.PP
Each output line has the format

.PP
\fBOUTPUT_NAME DPI WIDTH_PX HEIGHT_PX\fR

.PP
The file is updated whenever monitors are hot-plugged or display parameters
change.
.SH FILES
.I /var/cache/wayland-display-info/display-info
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR wayland-font-dpi (1)
.SH EXAMPLES
.B Check service status
.PP
.nf
systemctl --user status wayland-display-info.service
cat /var/cache/wayland-display-info/display-info
.fi
